        <p> On Sunday we drove the R1 bus to Lantau, where we looked at a huge Buddha. 
			One should not ask Google Maps for the purpose of the direction. 
			This once sent us around a circle via the public, as we noticed, because we landed 2 stations later exactly where we originally came from.
			Public transport is so cheap here, so it is really fun.
			The 1.5 hour drive with the Express bus only cost a mere $ 43HK (approx. 5 &euro;).
			A little expensive for Hong Kong.
			A ferry trip, on the other hand, only costs $ 4.3hk for the upscale class. So only 10%. </p>
