	      <p> Lantau is an island in front of Hong Kong where the new airport was also built.
			There is a huge Buddha stature on the top of the mountain.
			Depending on the start/landing direction, Buddha can even be seen very well from the plane.
			When we arrived up there by bus, there was relatively little going on on the mountain.
			So we were able to look around in peace.
			There is not only Buddha itself and various shops up there, but even a Buddhist monastery.
			If you want, you can (of course for a fee) pray with the monks or eat with them.
			We were a little bit of a vocals and since we don't like smacking and sipping, we simply shared a portion of pasta with vegetables on the snack bar.
			Animals are also available here, cattle to say exactly, as well as free -living. 
			These run freely all over the island and are eagerly waiting for their soft drink (see picture).
			Incidentally, these are also trusting and "like" are available for pictures and pats. </p>
        <p> Back to Hong Kong we took a boat in the evening.
			Unfortunately without a view, since the windows were crusted by the salt water. </p>  
